The 57-year-old man who received a pig’s heart in replacement of his own failing one has died two months after his historic transplant. David Bennett died on Tuesday, according to the University of Maryland Medical Center, which is where he received the transplant in early January and had been recovering ever since. Bennett’s health had been on the decline in recent days, though it’s unclear what caused his death. He was the first patient ever to receive an animal organ genetically modified to prevent rejection in a person. This is a breaking news story, check back for updates… Receive top breaking news, events, ideas, and more!